                           Project 2 -  Boolean Arithmetic
                           -----------------------------
  

Submitted Files
---------------
README - description of the project
Add16.hdl - Adds two 16-bit values.
ALU.hdl - The ALU (Arithmetic Logic Unit).
FullAdder.hdl - Computes the sum of three bits.
HalfAdder.hdl - Computes the sum of two bits.
Inc16.hdl - 16-bit incrementer.
Mul.hdl - Multiplication of two 16-bit numbers chip.
Aid chips for Mul:
	Abs.hdl - Returns the absolute value of a 16-bit number and a flag indicating the number's original sign.
	PMul.hdl - Multiplies two positive numbers.
	Negator.hdl - Returns the the 16-bit number times -1.
ShiftLeft.hdl - Multiplies a 16-bit number by 2.
ShiftRight.hdl - Divides a 16-bit number by 2.

Remarks
-------
We implemented 3 different chips that are used as inside chips for the Multiplication chip (as described above).
In our implementation, we turn the two numbers to positive numbers using the Abs chip, multiply them using the PMul
chip, and than use the Negator chip according to the input's original sign inorder to fix the result's sign.